/**
 * Steel section databases.
 *
 * IPE_SECTIONS – IPE I-beams (EN 10365, hot-rolled).
 *   h, b, tf, tw, R  – dimensions (mm)
 *   A                – cross-section area (mm²)
 *   Aw               – shear area (elastic) (mm²)
 *   Wy               – elastic section modulus, strong axis (mm³)
 *   Zy               – plastic section modulus, strong axis (mm³)
 *   Iy               – second moment of area, strong axis (mm⁴)
 *   g                – self-weight (kg/m)
 *
 * VKR_SECTIONS – Rectangular/Square Hollow Sections, hot-finished (EN 10210).
 *   h, b, t          – outer height, outer width, wall thickness (mm)
 *   A                – cross-section area (mm²)
 *   Iy, Iz           – second moments of area, strong/weak axis (mm⁴)
 *   Wy, Wz           – elastic section moduli (mm³)
 *   Zy, Zz           – plastic section moduli (mm³)  [only for class 1/2 keys]
 *   iy, iz           – radii of gyration (mm)
 *   Av               – shear area for loading in h-direction: 2×h×t (mm²)
 *   g                – self-weight (kg/m)
 *
 * All values are exact tabulated data from EN 10365 (IPE, HEA, HEB, HEM) and
 * EN 10210 (VKR/KKR hollow sections).
 */

